definitions.definition: The righthand side of a ship, boat or aircraft when facing the front, or fore or bow . Used to unambiguously refer to directions according to the sides of the vessel, rather than those of a crew member or object.
examples: I see another vessel off the starboard side.
We're on starboard tack, so the other boat has to give way.

definitions.definition: ( nautical ) One of the two traditional watches aboard a ship standing a watch in two .

A system that enables such a list.
